article.headline: Weber St. 78, Portland St. 68
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Kellen McCoy scored 16 points, including six free throws in the final 1:11, to lead Weber State to a 78-68 win over Portland State on Saturday night. Damian Lillard added 14 points, while Nick Hansen finished with 12 for the Wildcats (17-8, 11-1 Big Sky). With the score tied at 17-17 midway through the first half, Weber State used a pair of 8-0 runs to take control and go into the break with a 38-29 lead. But the Vikings (17-9, 8-5) got back into the game with an 8-1 run that started and ended with 3-pointers from Jeremiah Dominguez. That brought the Vikings to within 39-37 three minutes into the second half, but they could get no closer. Dominguez led Portland State with a game-high 22 points, followed by Dominic Waters with 12 and Kyle Coston and Julius Thomas with 10 points apiece. The win gave the Wildcats a season sweep over the defending Big Sky Conference champions.
